graph TD
    subgraph OSI Model
        direction TB
        L7[Layer 7: Application<br/>e.g., HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS]
        L6[Layer 6: Presentation<br/>e.g., SSL/TLS Encryption, JPEG, ASCII]
        L5[Layer 5: Session<br/>e.g., NetBIOS, SAP, Session Cookies]
        L4[Layer 4: Transport<br/>e.g., TCP (Reliable), UDP (Fast)]
        L3[Layer 3: Network<br/>e.g., IP Addresses, Routers, ICMP]
        L2[Layer 2: Data Link<br/>e.g., MAC Addresses, Switches, Ethernet]
        L1[Layer 1: Physical<br/>e.g., Cables, Hubs, Wi-Fi Radio Waves]
    end

    L7 -- Data --> L6
    L6 -- Data --> L5
    L5 -- Data --> L4
    L4 -- Segments/Datagrams --> L3
    L3 -- Packets --> L2
    L2 -- Frames --> L1
    L1 -- Bits --> L_Physical_Medium((Physical Medium))
    
